descp2: If indices_or_sections is an integer, N, the array will be divided into N equal arrays along axis.  If such a split is not possible, an error is raised. If indices_or_sections is a 1-D array of sorted integers, the entries indicate where along axis the array is split.  For example, `[2, 3]` would, for `axis=0`, result in - ary[:2] - ary[2:3] - ary[3:] If an index exceeds the dimension of the array along axis, an empty sub-array is returned correspondingly.
